description: Code review and pull request standards
alwaysApply: false
---

# Cursor Rules: Code Review & PR Standards

rules:
  - id: code_review.pr.requirements
    description: |
      Pull requests must meet minimum requirements before review.
      - PRs must have clear, descriptive titles
      - PRs must include description explaining changes and rationale
      - PRs must link to related issues or tickets
      - PRs must pass all CI/CD checks (tests, linting, type checking)
      - PRs must not decrease test coverage below thresholds
      - PRs must include appropriate documentation updates
    severity: error

  - id: code_review.pr.templates
    description: |
      Pull requests must use standardized templates.
      - Use PR template with required sections
      - Include checklist of requirements
      - Document breaking changes clearly
      - Include testing instructions
      - Document migration steps if applicable
      - Keep PR template up-to-date
    severity: warning

  - id: code_review.pr.size
    description: |
      Pull requests must be appropriately sized.
      - Keep PRs focused on a single feature or fix
      - Split large changes into multiple smaller PRs
      - Aim for PRs that can be reviewed in <30 minutes
      - Document rationale for large PRs
      - Use feature flags for large feature additions
    severity: warning

  - id: code_review.review.criteria
    description: |
      Code reviews must evaluate specific criteria.
      - Code correctness and functionality
      - Adherence to coding standards and style
      - Test coverage and quality
      - Documentation completeness
      - Performance implications
      - Security considerations
      - Architecture and design decisions
    severity: error

  - id: code_review.review.approval
    description: |
      Code review approval requirements must be enforced.
      - Require at least one approval for non-critical changes
      - Require multiple approvals for critical changes
      - Require approval from code owners for their areas
      - Require approval from security team for security-sensitive changes
      - Document approval requirements in repository settings
    severity: error

  - id: code_review.review.feedback
    description: |
      Code review feedback must be constructive and actionable.
      - Provide specific, actionable feedback
      - Explain reasoning behind suggestions
      - Suggest improvements, not just point out problems
      - Be respectful and professional
      - Respond to feedback promptly
      - Resolve discussions before merging
    severity: warning

  - id: code_review.merge.policies
    description: |
      Merge policies must be clearly defined and enforced.
      - Require passing CI/CD checks before merge
      - Require code review approvals before merge
      - Use merge strategies appropriate for project (squash, rebase, merge commit)
      - Enforce branch protection rules
      - Document merge policies in repository settings
    severity: error

  - id: code_review.merge.cleanup
    description: |
      Branches must be cleaned up after merge.
      - Delete feature branches after merge
      - Keep main/master branch clean
      - Document branch retention policies
      - Use branch naming conventions
    severity: warning

  - id: code_review.branch.naming
    description: |
      Branch names must follow consistent conventions.
      - Use descriptive branch names
      - Include issue/ticket numbers when applicable
      - Use prefixes for branch types (feature/, fix/, hotfix/, etc.)
      - Use kebab-case for branch names
      - Document branch naming conventions
    severity: warning

  - id: code_review.commit.messages
    description: |
      Commit messages must follow conventional commit format.
      - Use clear, descriptive commit messages
      - Follow conventional commit format (type: description)
      - Include issue/ticket references
      - Explain why, not just what
      - Use imperative mood in commit messages
      - Keep commit messages concise but informative
    severity: error

  - id: code_review.commit.history
    description: |
      Commit history must be clean and meaningful.
      - Squash or rebase commits before merging when appropriate
      - Group related changes in single commits
      - Avoid "WIP" or "fix typo" commits in final history
      - Use meaningful commit messages
      - Keep commit history linear when possible
    severity: warning

examples:
  - description: "PR template example"
    language: markdown
    code: |
      ## Description
      
      Brief description of changes and rationale.
      
      ## Related Issues
      
      - Closes #123
      - Related to #456
      
      ## Type of Change
      
      - [ ] Bug fix
      - [ ] New feature
      - [ ] Breaking change
      - [ ] Documentation update
      - [ ] Performance improvement
      - [ ] Refactoring
      
      ## Testing
      
      - [ ] Tests added/updated
      - [ ] All tests pass
      - [ ] Manual testing completed
      
      ## Checklist
      
      - [ ] Code follows style guidelines
      - [ ] Self-review completed
      - [ ] Comments added for complex code
      - [ ] Documentation updated
      - [ ] No new warnings generated
      - [ ] Breaking changes documented
      
      ## Breaking Changes
      
      If this PR includes breaking changes, describe them here:
      
      ## Additional Notes
      
      Any additional information for reviewers.

  - description: "Conventional commit message format"
    language: text
    code: |
      feat(api): add authentication middleware
      
      Add authentication middleware for API endpoints with support
      for optional and required authentication modes.
      
      - Implement API key validation
      - Add authentication dependency injection
      - Support MAVAIA_REQUIRE_AUTH environment variable
      
      Closes #123

  - description: "Branch naming examples"
    language: text
    code: |
      feature/add-metrics-tracking
      fix/api-timeout-handling
      hotfix/security-patch
      refactor/module-registry
      docs/update-api-docs
      test/add-integration-tests

references:
  - Conventional Commits: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
  - GitHub PR templates: https://docs.github.com/en/communities/using-templates-to-encourage-useful-issues-and-pull-requests
  - Code review best practices: https://google.github.io/eng-practices/review/
